# Keep the Docker build context lean (matters most in CI, where the whole
# context is uploaded to the builder). The image build only needs the Go module,
# the source tree, internal/tracer's BPF C source, the external/nsjail submodule,
# and configs/ — none of the frontend, e2e, or VCS data below.
#
# Do NOT add external/, configs/, go.mod, go.sum, or any *.go / *.c here: the
# multi-stage build's `COPY . .` (Go build + go generate) and the final
# `COPY configs/` depend on them.
.git
.github
web
.e2e
dist
docs
*.exe
goboxd
tracebox
tracebox-mcp
**/node_modules
